♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.886 --> 01:47.107
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:39.898 --> 02:41.857
-[WATER TRICKLING]

02:45.165 --> 02:46.688
-MOM?

02:48.733 --> 02:51.345
MOM! MOM?

02:59.527 --> 03:01.746
MOM! MOM?

03:10.842 --> 03:13.584
MOM! MOM, WAKE UP.

03:13.715 --> 03:14.759
MOM.

03:15.630 --> 03:17.284
OH, MY GOD. MOM...

03:18.067 --> 03:19.547
-MAN ON RADIO:
THIS IS BAYWATCH SCARAB.

03:19.677 --> 03:21.331
EN ROUTE TO CRASH SITE,
CODE THREE.

03:21.462 --> 03:23.246
ETA, TWO MINUTES.

03:38.087 --> 03:40.176
-MAN ON RADIO:
COAST GUARD AIR RESCUE
TO BAYWATCH SCARAB...

03:40.307 --> 03:41.743
WE'RE ON ROUTE TO ASSIST.

03:41.873 --> 03:43.527
ETA, FIVE MINUTES.

03:53.537 --> 03:56.453
-MAN ON RADIO: US COAST GUARD
CUTTER POINT BRIDGE
TO BAYWATCH SCARAB...

03:56.584 --> 03:58.934
RESPONDING TO APPROXIMATE
COORDINATES OF IMPACT.

04:08.291 --> 04:09.814
-OH!

04:11.729 --> 04:13.818
KEN! KEN!

04:15.777 --> 04:16.952
OUCH!

04:18.997 --> 04:21.348
KEN! KEN! KEN!

04:21.478 --> 04:22.827
KEN! MY MOM, SHE'S ALIVE.

04:22.958 --> 04:24.742
SHE'S GOT A PULSE,
BUT SHE'S HURT.

04:24.873 --> 04:26.614
-KEN!
-YEAH?

04:26.744 --> 04:29.051
-COME ON, I NEED YOUR HELP.
COME ON.

04:29.181 --> 04:30.444
COME ON.

04:31.227 --> 04:32.663
-[GROANS] YEAH.

04:33.664 --> 04:34.883
YEAH.

04:41.498 --> 04:43.544
-STOP, KEN! DON'T!

04:43.674 --> 04:45.633
-WE GOTTA GET OUT
OF HERE BEFORE THE FIRE.

04:46.242 --> 04:48.505
-KEN, WE'RE UNDERWATER.
IF YOU OPEN THE DOOR,
WE'LL ALL DROWN!

04:49.506 --> 04:51.813
-IT WON'T OPEN!

04:51.943 --> 04:54.729
-THE PRESSURE... THE DOOR
WON'T OPEN UNLESS THE PRESSURE'S
THE SAME ON BOTH SIDES.

04:54.859 --> 04:57.122
MY MOM NEEDS YOU.
-[COUGHING]

05:13.835 --> 05:14.705
-OH, MY GOD.

05:15.358 --> 05:16.403
-SHE'S STUCK!

05:17.447 --> 05:19.057
KEN, PLEASE!

05:19.928 --> 05:21.364
-I'LL RADIO FOR HELP!

05:54.702 --> 05:56.573
-[GRUNTING]

06:03.798 --> 06:04.668
-DID YOU RADIO?

06:05.800 --> 06:06.714
-IT'S DEAD.

06:09.281 --> 06:10.805
AND SO IS ELANE.

06:14.983 --> 06:17.072
WE'RE ALL GONNA DIE DOWN HERE.

06:17.202 --> 06:19.596
-MY DAD WAS ON THE PHONE.
HE KNOWS WHAT HAPPENED.

06:19.727 --> 06:21.163
-THE PHONE!

06:34.437 --> 06:35.830
-MOM!

06:35.960 --> 06:37.527
-WHERE THE HELL
IS THE DAMN OXYGEN?

06:58.940 --> 07:00.332
-MITCH, OVER THERE!

07:01.682 --> 07:03.727
-[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

07:13.694 --> 07:14.999
-THE PLANE,
THEY CRASHED OVER THERE!

07:18.699 --> 07:20.091
-DID YOU SEE IT?

07:24.400 --> 07:26.184
-BAYWATCH RESCUE
TO COAST GUARD.

07:31.189 --> 07:32.408
-[GROANS]

07:33.017 --> 07:35.542
-MOM! MOM, ARE YOU OKAY?

07:37.544 --> 07:38.675
-WHAT HAPPENED?

07:38.806 --> 07:40.242
-WE HAD TO LAND IN THE OCEAN.

07:40.895 --> 07:42.679
WE'RE UNDERWATER,
BUT WE HAVE AIR.

07:42.810 --> 07:46.596
-FOR HOW LONG?
THIS PLANE'S LEAKING
LIKE A SIEVE.

07:46.727 --> 07:49.730
-SHUT UP! JUST SHUT UP!
YOU'RE SCARING MY MOM!

07:52.863 --> 07:54.865
-MITCH: I DON'T CARE,
THE PLANE'S SUBMERGED.

07:54.996 --> 07:56.998
MAKE SURE OUR FLOTATION GEAR
GETS ABOARD
THE COAST GUARD CUTTER.

07:57.128 --> 07:59.043
WE NEED IT FAST.

07:59.174 --> 08:01.611
-THE FISHERMEN SAW THE PLANE
GO DOWN ABOUT 50 YARDS
OFF OUR STARBOARD BOW.

08:05.136 --> 08:06.007
-KEN.

08:08.096 --> 08:08.966
KEN!

08:09.097 --> 08:10.533
-SHE'S CALLING YOU.

08:17.975 --> 08:19.324
-LISTEN, I'M HERE, BABY.

08:19.455 --> 08:20.674
-KEN...

08:26.636 --> 08:28.551
-SHE'S STUCK.
HELP ME PULL THIS OFF.

08:32.076 --> 08:33.337
-HOBIE...

08:33.469 --> 08:34.948
-YOU'RE GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT, MOM.

08:35.078 --> 08:37.125
PUSH HARDER!

08:46.438 --> 08:47.614
-THERE!

09:37.968 --> 09:39.927
-GET OVER HERE AND
HELP ME PLUG THESE LEAKS.

09:40.057 --> 09:41.406
-I CAN'T LEAVE MY MOM.

09:41.537 --> 09:44.540
-WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES THAT
MAKE IF SHE'S GONNA DROWN?

09:47.935 --> 09:48.936
-MOM?

09:49.850 --> 09:53.027
-MITCH... MITCH WILL COME.

09:54.419 --> 09:56.030
-WHAT IS SHE SAYING?

09:57.161 --> 09:58.815
-MITCH WILL COME.

09:58.946 --> 10:00.643
-WHAT IS SHE SAYING?

10:00.774 --> 10:02.776
-SHE'S CALLING FOR MY DAD,
NOT FOR YOU!

10:05.735 --> 10:07.607
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY, MOM.

10:09.173 --> 10:10.958
-STEPHANIE: GIVE ME AN ETA.
-MITCH: NEWMIE!

10:11.611 --> 10:14.004
IF THE PLANE'S STILL INTACT.
WE MIGHT NEED AN OXYGEN
LINE DOWN THERE.

10:14.135 --> 10:15.963
GET ME A DRILL.
-YOU GOT IT.

10:16.703 --> 10:19.053
-HURRY UP! COME ON,
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

10:22.056 --> 10:24.798
-MITCH, MAYBE YOU SHOULD
STAY UP HERE TILL THE OTHERS
CHECK IT OUT.

10:24.928 --> 10:27.148
-YOU CRAZY?
THAT'S MY SON
DOWN THERE.

10:28.236 --> 10:29.759
GET THAT AIR SUPPLY READY.

11:09.190 --> 11:11.279
-MOM, DON'T CLOSE YOUR EYES.

11:11.409 --> 11:13.324
YOU HAVE TO STAY AWAKE.

11:13.455 --> 11:15.805
HELP ME GET THIS OFF HER,
BEFORE THE WATER GOES
OVER HER HEAD.

11:16.458 --> 11:18.025
-IF YOU LET HER SLEEP...

11:18.155 --> 11:19.374
SHE WON'T SUFFER.

11:20.636 --> 11:23.291
-DON'T GIVE UP.
WE CAN'T GIVE UP.

11:24.814 --> 11:26.294
-I THINK...

11:26.424 --> 11:28.252
WE SHOULD ALL PRAY.

11:49.230 --> 11:50.492
-MITCH...

11:54.104 --> 11:54.975
-WHAT?

11:58.065 --> 11:59.414
-MITCH.

12:00.241 --> 12:01.416
-DAD?

12:12.209 --> 12:14.516
DAD! DAD!

12:19.608 --> 12:21.001
-HEY!

12:21.131 --> 12:22.132
COME ON!

12:27.224 --> 12:28.138
-DAD!

12:28.269 --> 12:30.184
-GET US OUT OF HERE!

12:30.314 --> 12:32.142
-DAD, HURRY UP.
MOM'S HURT...

12:32.273 --> 12:34.710
[INDISTINCT]

12:36.233 --> 12:37.800
SHE CAN'T MOVE!

13:01.824 --> 13:02.956
-WE'RE HERE!

14:20.163 --> 14:22.426
-WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
COME BACK!

14:25.603 --> 14:27.431
WHERE ARE THEY GOING?

14:51.281 --> 14:53.762
COME HERE!
COME BACK AND GET US!

15:00.769 --> 15:03.815
-MOM, DAD'S HERE
WITH THE LIFEGUARDS.
THEY'LL GET US OUT.

15:04.468 --> 15:06.209
DON'T WORRY.
-WHERE ARE THEY GOING?

15:06.340 --> 15:08.951
-STAY CALM.
WE HAVE AIR COMING IN.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.433
-WHERE THE HELL ARE THEY GOING?

15:12.563 --> 15:14.783
-TO GET WHAT THEY
NEED TO SAVE US.

15:19.744 --> 15:21.572
I KNEW DAD WOULD COME.

15:30.451 --> 15:31.626
-MITCH!

15:33.497 --> 15:35.282
-YEAH? WHAT'VE YOU GOT?

15:35.412 --> 15:37.197
-I'VE GOT YOUR FLOTATION BOTTLE,
BUT IT MAY NOT FIT THAT PLANE.

15:37.327 --> 15:38.894
-NO TIME TO EXPERIMENT.

15:39.025 --> 15:41.375
-MITCH, YOU'VE GOT TO TRY.
IT'S OUR BEST CHANCE.

15:41.505 --> 15:43.377
-IT'LL TAKE 15-20
MINUTES TO RIG.

15:43.507 --> 15:45.379
-NO, I'VE BEEN DOWN THERE.
THAT'S TOO MUCH TIME.

15:45.509 --> 15:47.598
GAYLE'S PINNED.

15:47.729 --> 15:49.383
SHE'LL BE UNDERWATER BY THEN.

15:49.513 --> 15:51.994
NEWMIE, GIVE ME
THREE BOTTLES OF
SPARE AIR.

15:53.517 --> 15:56.390
-WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?
-YOU GUYS GOT ANY
CUTTING TOOLS ON BOARD?

15:56.520 --> 15:58.261
AIR CHISEL?
-YEAH. WE DO!

15:58.392 --> 16:00.785
-OKAY.
-MITCH, THAT'S TOO DANGEROUS.

16:00.916 --> 16:02.526
-NEWMIE, LET'S GO!

16:03.484 --> 16:05.051
-LOOK, THE COMPARTMENT
WILL FLOOD.

16:05.181 --> 16:07.270
-NOT IF THE AIR POCKET HOLDS
UNTIL WE'RE INSIDE.

16:07.401 --> 16:10.404
-MITCH!
-WHEN IT'S YOUR SON DOWN THERE,
YOU DO IT YOUR WAY, HUH?

16:10.534 --> 16:12.710
COME ON, NEWMIE!

16:12.841 --> 16:14.538
-WE'LL START RIGGING
THE FLOTATION GEAR,
IN CASE YOU NEED IT. GOOD LUCK.

16:29.379 --> 16:31.077
-WATER'S RISING FAST.

16:45.656 --> 16:48.529
-MOM? MOM?

16:48.659 --> 16:50.096
MOM, YOU GOTTA STAY AWAKE.

16:51.358 --> 16:52.663
MOM!

17:02.630 --> 17:05.633
REMEMBER THE TIME,
ME AND YOU AND DAD
WENT TO THE GRAND CANYON...

17:05.762 --> 17:07.722
AND WE RODE MULES DOWN...

17:07.852 --> 17:09.202
AND DAD FELL OFF...

17:10.029 --> 17:11.856
AND HE DRAGGED HIM
ALL THE WAY DOWN.

17:13.597 --> 17:14.642
-AND I SAID...

17:15.772 --> 17:18.559
YOU NEVER TAKE
A VACATION WITH DAD...

17:18.689 --> 17:20.169
AWAY FROM WATER.

17:27.872 --> 17:29.483
I LOVE YOU, HOBIE.

17:29.613 --> 17:31.050
-I LOVE YOU, TOO.

17:35.793 --> 17:37.708
-WHERE THE HELL ARE YOU?

17:55.683 --> 17:57.902
-[INDISTINCT TALKING ON RADIO]

18:03.778 --> 18:06.998
♪ MY LOVE KNOWS NO BOUNDS

18:08.478 --> 18:11.612
♪ COME DANGER OR STRIFE

18:14.702 --> 18:17.966
♪ I'D WALK A MILLION MILES

18:18.097 --> 18:21.317
♪ TO BE THE AIR THAT YOU BREATHE

18:24.451 --> 18:28.019
♪ I WILL BE THERE FOR YOU

18:29.108 --> 18:34.765
♪ YOU KNOW I'LL BE THERE FOR YOU...OHHH

18:37.681 --> 18:40.467
♪ WHATEVER IT TAKES

18:41.990 --> 18:45.385
♪ WHEREVER THE FIGHT

18:48.083 --> 18:51.782
♪ I'D MOVE THE MOUNTAINS OHHH

18:51.913 --> 18:54.089
♪ JUST TO GET TO YOU

18:56.439 --> 18:59.703
♪ THE MOON AND THE STARS

19:01.227 --> 19:04.143
♪ THEY ALL WOULD AGREE

19:07.102 --> 19:10.497
♪ I'D SACRIFICE IT ALL

19:11.585 --> 19:13.717
-YOU'LL BE OKAY, MOM.
YOU CAN BREATHE THROUGH THIS.

19:16.633 --> 19:20.420
♪ I WILL BE THERE FOR YOU

19:21.638 --> 19:25.468
♪ YOU KNOW I'LL BE THERE FOR YOU

19:26.861 --> 19:28.602
♪ OHHH

19:29.690 --> 19:33.737
♪ I'LL BE THERE FOR YOU...

19:35.348 --> 19:37.524
♪ OHHH

19:39.874 --> 19:44.052
♪ THERE FOR YOU

19:44.792 --> 19:47.186
-KEN, GET OVER HERE!
MY MOM'S NOT BREATHING.

19:48.839 --> 19:52.800
♪ I'LL BE THERE FOR YOU

19:54.193 --> 19:57.370
♪ OHHH

19:58.849 --> 20:02.940
♪ THERE FOR YOU

20:03.941 --> 20:09.382
♪ OHHH

20:09.512 --> 20:11.906
♪ WHATEVER IT TAKES

20:12.036 --> 20:16.867
♪ WHATEVER THE STAKES OHHHH

20:18.652 --> 20:21.698
♪ I'LL BE THERE WHEN YOU NEED ME

20:21.829 --> 20:26.486
♪ PARTING THE SEAS OHHHH

20:37.018 --> 20:40.978
♪ I'LL BE THERE FOR YOU

20:45.635 --> 20:47.246
-HOBIE!

20:47.376 --> 20:50.118
-DAD! DAD, COME HERE.
MOM'S NOT BREATHING! HURRY!

21:17.841 --> 21:19.974
-HELP ME GET OUT OF HERE!
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO!

21:20.104 --> 21:21.454
-IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.

21:21.584 --> 21:22.933
NEWMIE, HELP!

21:24.718 --> 21:27.024
-SHE'S TRAPPED UNDERWATER.
SHE CAN'T BREATHE.

21:37.905 --> 21:39.298
-SHE'S UNCONSCIOUS.

21:39.428 --> 21:41.996
-GET UP. GET ME UP!
-COME HERE, MAN.

21:42.126 --> 21:44.564
JUST CALM DOWN.
CALM DOWN, MAN.

21:44.694 --> 21:46.609
JUST PUT THIS IN YOUR MOUTH.

21:46.740 --> 21:50.004
-HERE TAKE THIS.
-NO, I WANT TO STAY WITH MOM.

22:15.812 --> 22:16.987
-GO ON. C.J.!

22:17.118 --> 22:19.033
GO ON! GET OUT OF HERE!

22:19.816 --> 22:21.862
-I'LL STAY WITH MOM.
-HOBIE, COME ON.

22:21.992 --> 22:23.994
-MOM!
-NEWMIE!

22:24.908 --> 22:27.868
-MOM!
-HOBIE, IT'S GONNA BE OKAY,
YOUR DAD'S GOT HER.

22:27.998 --> 22:30.000
OKAY, NOW YOU KNOW
HOW TO USE ONE OF
THOSE THINGS, RIGHT?

22:30.131 --> 22:31.741
-YEAH.
-OKAY, NOW JUST RELAX.

22:32.394 --> 22:33.700
-WE GOTTA LIFT THIS THING!

22:33.830 --> 22:35.266
-WE'RE GONNA GO DOWN ON THREE.

22:35.397 --> 22:37.225
OKAY? READY?
OKAY, RELAX.

22:39.749 --> 22:41.969
TWO...THREE!

24:18.500 --> 24:21.895
-MAN ON RADIO: ROGER, MEDEVAC.
BRINGING THE MALE PASSENGER
ON BOARD.

24:23.418 --> 24:25.289
-COAST GUARD'S SAYING
THEY'RE READY TO HOIST AGAIN...

24:25.420 --> 24:27.335
RESCUE BASKET
OR STOKES LITTER.

24:27.466 --> 24:29.859
-TELL 'EM WE'RE GONNA
START CPR, AND WE'RE
TAKING HER IN...

24:29.990 --> 24:31.470
THREE AS THE
DECOMPRESSION CHAMBER.

24:32.079 --> 24:34.081
GO! AND HAVE THE PARAMEDICS
MEET US AT THE DOCK.

24:34.690 --> 24:35.691
-GET HER AIRWAY CLEAR.

24:35.822 --> 24:36.866
-GIVE ME A BP CUFF.

24:36.997 --> 24:39.782
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE!

24:48.530 --> 24:50.706
-MITCH: THREE, FOUR, FIVE...

24:52.012 --> 24:53.622
-STEPHANIE:
GET HER BLOUSE OPEN!

24:56.930 --> 24:59.628
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE...
-STILL NO RESPIRATION.

24:59.759 --> 25:02.588
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE...

25:02.718 --> 25:04.807
-SHE'S ASPIRATING.
GET HER IN LEFT
LATERAL POSITION.

25:04.938 --> 25:07.114
-MOM, PLEASE BREATHE.

25:07.244 --> 25:08.245
-STEPHANIE: ASPIRATE!

25:10.509 --> 25:12.946
NO PULSE! WE NEED
THE DEFIBRILLATOR.

25:13.076 --> 25:15.862
-MITCH: GO AND TELL
THE PARAMEDICS TO HAVE
THE ADRENALIN READY.

25:15.992 --> 25:17.037
-AIRWAY CLEAR.

25:17.690 --> 25:18.995
-STEPHANIE: RESUME CPR!

25:19.648 --> 25:22.303
-MITCH: ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

25:22.433 --> 25:24.740
-STEPHANIE:
PREPARING DEFIB PADS.
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE!

25:24.871 --> 25:26.786
-C.J.: O2 READY.

25:26.916 --> 25:28.788
-MITCH: COME ON, GAYLE.
FOUR, FIVE.

25:28.918 --> 25:31.878
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

25:32.008 --> 25:35.098
-C.J.: MASK ON.
-ONE, TWO...
COME ON, BABE. COME ON.

25:35.229 --> 25:37.448
-FIVE!
-O2 ON.

25:37.579 --> 25:39.973
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

25:40.103 --> 25:42.366
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

25:42.497 --> 25:43.498
-MOM, PLEASE!

25:43.629 --> 25:47.023
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

25:47.154 --> 25:50.287
-BP CUFF ON.
-ANALYZE, READY TO TEST.

25:50.418 --> 25:52.072
STOP CPR.

25:52.202 --> 25:55.075
-AUTOMATED VOICE:
STAND CLEAR! STAND CLEAR!

25:55.205 --> 25:56.990
-STEPHANIE: CHARGING!

25:58.426 --> 26:00.167
-HOBIE!

26:00.297 --> 26:01.560
-NO SHOCKABLE RHYTHM.

26:01.690 --> 26:03.300
-AUTOMATED VOICE:
CHECK PATIENT! CHECK PATIENT!

26:05.825 --> 26:07.740
-NO PULSE. RESUME CPR.

26:09.176 --> 26:11.744
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.
-C.J.: VENTILATING.

26:11.874 --> 26:14.660
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

26:15.225 --> 26:17.750
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE!

26:18.446 --> 26:19.969
-SECOND ANALYZE.

26:20.100 --> 26:22.406
-AUTOMATED VOICE:
STAND CLEAR! STAND CLEAR!

26:23.407 --> 26:25.714
-CHARGING!
-AUTOMATED VOICE:
CHECK PATIENT! CHECK PATIENT!

26:25.845 --> 26:27.020
-NOT SHOCKABLE.

26:27.150 --> 26:28.891
-CHECK PATIENT! CHECK PATIENT!

26:30.414 --> 26:32.547
-NO PULSE.
CONTINUE CPR.

26:33.504 --> 26:35.985
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

26:36.116 --> 26:38.292
COME ON.

26:38.422 --> 26:40.076
DAMN IT. COME ON, GAYLE!

26:40.207 --> 26:42.470
TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

26:42.601 --> 26:45.212
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.
-STEPHANIE:
INCREASE VENTILATION.

26:45.342 --> 26:48.868
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.
-MOM, PLEASE!

26:48.998 --> 26:50.260
-THIRD ANALYZE.

26:50.391 --> 26:53.263
-AUTOMATED VOICE:
STAND CLEAR! STAND CLEAR!

26:53.394 --> 26:55.526
-CHARGING!
-STAND CLEAR! STAND CLEAR!

26:55.657 --> 26:56.963
-SHE'S SHOCKABLE.

27:00.967 --> 27:03.360
-AUTOMATED VOICE:
PRESS TO SHOCK! PRESS TO SHOCK!
-STEPHANIE: SHOCKING!

27:14.197 --> 27:15.198
SHE'S GOT A PULSE!

27:16.896 --> 27:18.898
-YEAH, BABY.
YEAH, BABY.

27:37.873 --> 27:40.310
-[ANNOUNCEMENTS ON PA]

27:52.758 --> 27:53.889
-DAD!

27:56.065 --> 27:57.850
-SHE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.
-ALL RIGHT!

27:58.502 --> 28:00.635
-HOW'S KEN?
-THE DOCTOR SAYS
HE'LL BE FINE.

28:00.766 --> 28:02.115
-YEAH... NOW.

28:02.811 --> 28:04.465
-WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

28:04.595 --> 28:06.162
-DOWN THERE, ALL HE CARED
ABOUT WAS SAVING HIMSELF.

28:06.989 --> 28:09.165
HE WOULDN'T HELP MOM
UNTIL I MADE HIM.

28:12.865 --> 28:14.867
-WELL, WE BETTER
GET BACK TO THE BEACH.

28:15.737 --> 28:18.044
WE'LL CALL YOU LATER.
-YEAH. THANKS.

28:18.871 --> 28:20.568
-BYE.
-GIVE GAYLE MY LOVE.

28:20.699 --> 28:22.396
-YEAH, I WILL, C.J.. THANKS.
-I'LL SEE YOU LATER, OKAY?

28:22.526 --> 28:23.614
-OKAY, MATT.
-BYE!

28:24.920 --> 28:26.879
-HEY! YOU CAME THROUGH
WHEN IT COUNTED.

28:27.009 --> 28:28.271
WAY TO GO!

28:28.402 --> 28:29.533
-THANKS.

28:31.971 --> 28:33.363
HOPE YOU DON'T
MOVE TO FRANCE.

28:33.494 --> 28:35.148
-ME, TOO.
I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER, OKAY?

28:35.278 --> 28:36.715
-ALL RIGHT.
-SEE YOU.

28:37.324 --> 28:39.282
-CAN I GO SEE MOM NOW?
-YEAH, YEAH, SHE'S BEEN
ASKING FOR YOU.

28:39.413 --> 28:41.154
-YEAH, SHE WAS
ASKING FOR YOU, TOO.

28:42.242 --> 28:44.635
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
-DOWN THERE.
SHE CALLED YOUR NAME.

28:45.549 --> 28:47.029
COME ON, LET'S GO SEE HER.

28:52.818 --> 28:54.602
-MOM! MOM!

28:54.733 --> 28:56.604
-OH, HOBIE!

28:56.735 --> 28:57.823
OH, HONEY!

28:57.953 --> 29:00.521
CAREFUL, CAREFUL! OH!

29:01.217 --> 29:02.436
-HOW'RE YOU DOING?
-MITCH...

29:03.132 --> 29:04.917
OH, YOU SHOULD'VE
SEEN HIM DOWN THERE.

29:05.482 --> 29:07.180
YOU WOULD'VE BEEN
VERY PROUD OF YOUR SON.

29:07.310 --> 29:09.617
-YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN DAD.
HE WAS THE ONE THAT SAVED US.

29:09.748 --> 29:11.271
-OH!
-JUST PART OF A TEAM.

29:11.401 --> 29:13.316
-MY HEROES!

29:16.319 --> 29:18.278
MITCH, I WAS VERY
WRONG ABOUT HOBIE.

29:20.236 --> 29:22.195
HIS PLACE IS...

29:22.325 --> 29:23.370
IS HERE WITH YOU.

29:23.500 --> 29:25.938
AND CAN YOU EVER
FORGIVE ME?

29:27.069 --> 29:28.027
-ON ONE CONDITION...

29:29.332 --> 29:32.031
YOU PROMISE TO SPEND
MORE TIME OUT HERE WITH US.

29:32.161 --> 29:33.336
-YEAH.

29:35.164 --> 29:36.035
-OKAY.

29:39.342 --> 29:40.866
-HEY! WHAT IS THIS?

29:40.996 --> 29:42.650
OUT WITH THE NEW...
IN WITH THE OLD?

29:42.781 --> 29:46.045
-OH, KEN! THANK GOD
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT!

29:46.175 --> 29:48.090
I WAS SO WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

29:49.048 --> 29:50.092
-BABY...

29:52.703 --> 29:55.271
I LOVE YOU.
-YEAH. ME, TOO.

30:18.860 --> 30:20.079
-HEY!

30:20.644 --> 30:22.342
THAT'S MY BIKE!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

30:22.472 --> 30:24.039
-NO, IT'S NOT.

30:27.477 --> 30:28.827
-YOU NEVER STOP,
DO YOU, DAD?

30:29.915 --> 30:31.830
-I PAID FOR THIS
MOTORCYCLE, NOT YOU.

30:31.960 --> 30:35.268
NOW IF YOU CHOOSE
NOT TO COME TO FRANCE
WITH YOUR PARENTS, FINE.

30:35.398 --> 30:37.618
BUT DON'T EXPECT ME
TO CONTINUE TO SUPPORT
YOU HERE.

30:37.748 --> 30:39.185
-YOU KNOW...

30:39.881 --> 30:42.492
UNTIL NOW, I DIDN'T MAKE
A DECISION, IF I WANTED
TO STAY HERE OR NOT.

30:45.104 --> 30:47.019
THANKS FOR MAKING IT
SUCH AN EASY CHOICE.

30:47.628 --> 30:48.629
-MATT, WHAT'S WRONG?

30:48.759 --> 30:50.849
-MY FATHER'S
REPOSSESSING MY BIKE.

30:52.415 --> 30:53.895
IT'S HIS WAY OF SHOWING
HOW MUCH HE LOVES ME.

30:54.026 --> 30:55.288
-THAT'S RIGHT.

30:55.984 --> 30:57.594
YOU THINK YOU'RE GONNA
BE ABLE TO GO TO COLLEGE...

30:57.725 --> 30:59.945
AND SUPPORT YOURSELF ON
A PART-TIME LIFE GUARD JOB?

31:00.075 --> 31:01.337
-IF I HAVE TO.

31:01.468 --> 31:03.862
-WHERE ARE YOU GONNA LIVE?
-MATT CAN LIVE WITH US.

31:05.428 --> 31:07.039
-UH, STEPHANIE,
CAN WE TALK PLEASE?

31:07.169 --> 31:08.431
-I SEE.

31:08.562 --> 31:09.563
THREE'S COMPANY.

31:11.347 --> 31:13.175
-THESE PEOPLE ARE MORE
MY FAMILY THAN YOU ARE.

31:14.133 --> 31:15.308
SO GO AHEAD,
TAKE MY BIKE...

31:15.961 --> 31:17.397
TAKE EVERYTHING
YOU GAVE ME...

31:18.180 --> 31:19.965
AND TELL MOM--
-AND TELL MOM WHAT?

31:22.054 --> 31:23.229
-...THAT I LOVE HER.

31:31.019 --> 31:32.151
-SO YOU WANNA TAKE
CARE OF HIM, HUH?

31:32.978 --> 31:34.762
WELL, HAVE FUN.

31:34.893 --> 31:36.633
AND WHEN HE DOESN'T COME HOME
TILL 4:00 IN THE MORNING...

31:36.764 --> 31:37.983
YOU WAIT UP
AND WORRY.

31:38.809 --> 31:40.463
GET THE BIKE ON THE TRUCK.

31:44.337 --> 31:46.469
-MOM DOESN'T REMEMBER
HOW KEN ACTED.

31:46.600 --> 31:47.949
WHY DON'T WE TELL HER?

31:48.907 --> 31:50.560
-HOBIE, YOUR MOM LOVES HIM.

31:51.083 --> 31:52.823
JUST BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T
PANIC DOWN THERE--

31:52.954 --> 31:55.739
-HE SHOWED HIS TRUE COLORS, DAD.
BRIGHT YELLOW.

31:55.870 --> 31:59.265
-WELL, NOT EVERYBODY
COULD BE HEROIC IN LIFE
AND DEATH SITUATIONS.

31:59.395 --> 32:01.006
-MOM SHOULDN'T MARRY HIM.

32:01.136 --> 32:04.096
BESIDES, SHE STILL LOVES YOU,
AND YOU STILL LOVE HER.

32:04.226 --> 32:06.054
YOU GUYS SHOULD
GET MARRIED AGAIN.

32:06.185 --> 32:07.795
WE SHOULD BE A FAMILY.

32:07.926 --> 32:09.666
-WE ARE A FAMILY, PAL.

32:10.406 --> 32:12.104
YOU AND ME AND YOUR MOM.

32:12.234 --> 32:13.714
WE'LL ALWAYS BE A FAMILY.

32:13.844 --> 32:15.846
-THEN WHY CAN'T WE BE TOGETHER?

32:21.026 --> 32:24.333
-WHEN I THINK ABOUT
HOW CLOSE WE CAME TO BE
APART FOREVER, PAL--

32:25.813 --> 32:28.685
THANK GOD, I STILL GOT YOU.

32:30.600 --> 32:32.167
EVEN IF IT'S NOT
ALL THE TIME.

32:34.039 --> 32:35.823
-I DON'T THINK
KEN LOVES HER ENOUGH.

32:36.389 --> 32:39.218
I WOULD'VE DIED FOR MY MOM
AND YOU WOULD'VE, TOO,
I KNOW IT.

32:40.436 --> 32:41.960
I DON'T THINK
KEN WOULD'VE.

32:43.787 --> 32:45.702
MOM SHOULD KNOW
ABOUT IT, DAD.

33:01.414 --> 33:03.068
-KEN: COMING.
-GAYLE: JUST A SECOND.

33:05.244 --> 33:06.549
COME IN.

33:10.510 --> 33:11.467
MITCH...

33:20.563 --> 33:21.956
-HOBIE PICKED
THESE FOR YOU.

33:22.087 --> 33:23.871
-OH, THEY ARE
BEAUTIFUL.

33:25.003 --> 33:26.613
I'LL JUST STICK
THEM IN HERE.

33:27.831 --> 33:29.137
-LISTEN, MITCH...

33:29.703 --> 33:31.748
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO THANK YOU.
YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

33:32.967 --> 33:35.056
-YOUR LIFE WASN'T
THE ONLY ONE SAVED.

33:35.187 --> 33:36.492
-I KNOW.

33:37.406 --> 33:40.888
YOU SAVED THE WOMAN
THAT I LOVE MORE THAN
LIFE ITSELF.

33:42.324 --> 33:44.109
AND FOR THAT I WANT TO--

33:44.935 --> 33:46.676
LOOK, ANYTHING YOU WANT...

33:47.634 --> 33:48.852
YOU NAME IT,
IT'S YOURS.

33:51.420 --> 33:52.900
-MITCH, HE'S SERIOUS.

33:54.554 --> 33:56.121
-ALL I WANT IS...

33:57.774 --> 33:59.037
IS FOR YOU TO BE HAPPY.

33:59.167 --> 34:01.300
-I AM. I AM HAPPY.

34:01.430 --> 34:03.128
I MEAN, GOD, I'M ALIVE AND...

34:04.259 --> 34:07.741
I'M LUCKY ENOUGH TO BE
HERE WITH THE TWO MEN
WHO I LOVE VERY, VERY MUCH.

34:11.440 --> 34:13.833
KEN KNOWS HOW I FEEL.
HE KNOWS THAT...

34:14.617 --> 34:16.793
THAT I WANT NOTHING MORE
THAN TO BE HIS WIFE.

34:17.664 --> 34:20.493
BUT THAT I WILL ALWAYS
HAVE A VERY SPECIAL PLACE
IN MY HEART...

34:20.623 --> 34:21.623
THAT'S DEVOTED TO YOU.

34:27.630 --> 34:28.675
-HOW ABOUT YOU, KEN?

34:30.938 --> 34:33.592
HOW MUCH IS YOUR HEART
DEVOTED TO GAYLE?

34:33.723 --> 34:34.942
-ALL OF IT.

34:38.206 --> 34:40.774
-HOBIE TOLD ME HOW YOU
HANDLED THINGS AFTER
THE CRASH.

34:45.257 --> 34:46.127
-WHAT?

34:47.781 --> 34:48.869
-WHAT DID HE SAY?

35:02.056 --> 35:03.579
-DOESN'T MATTER NOW.

35:03.710 --> 35:05.973
-NO, OBVIOUSLY, IT DOES.
SO, WHY DON'T YOU TELL US?

35:08.628 --> 35:10.108
-HOBIE SAID THAT...

35:12.545 --> 35:14.416
KEN DIDN'T PANIC...

35:16.853 --> 35:19.856
THAT HE STAYED ON TOP
OF THINGS AND TOOK
GOOD CARE OF YOU.

35:24.948 --> 35:26.733
ALL I WANTED TO SAY WAS...

35:29.039 --> 35:32.478
I HOPE YOU TAKE EVEN
BETTER CARE OF GAYLE
IN THE FUTURE.

35:35.698 --> 35:37.657
-MITCH, HE WILL.

35:37.787 --> 35:40.486
GOD, KEN HAS TAKEN
WONDERFUL CARE OF ME
FROM THE MOMENT WE MET.

35:41.661 --> 35:42.749
-WELL...

35:43.402 --> 35:44.664
THAT'S WHAT MATTERS, ISN'T IT?

35:50.104 --> 35:52.585
I'M OUT OF HERE.
-I'D LIKE TO WALK YOU OUT.

36:02.334 --> 36:04.074
-THERE WILL ALWAYS BE...

36:05.380 --> 36:06.903
A SPECIAL PLACE...

36:07.730 --> 36:09.167
IN MY HEART...

36:10.385 --> 36:11.560
FOR YOU, TOO.

36:21.657 --> 36:23.181
-MITCH...

36:23.311 --> 36:24.486
I'M NOT A COWARD.

36:25.661 --> 36:27.272
I'M JUST NOT MUCH
OF A HERO.

36:29.099 --> 36:32.625
BUT I WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT I DO LOVE GAYLE
WITH ALL MY HEART.

36:35.018 --> 36:36.281
-TAKE CARE OF HER.

36:48.031 --> 36:50.556
-OH, SUMMER,
THIS IS A NIGHTMARE.

36:51.600 --> 36:55.430
IN ORDER TO START A BUSINESS,
YOU KNOW YOU HAVE TO DEAL WITH
FREDDY KRUEGER? UGH!

36:55.561 --> 36:58.564
AND EVERYTHING COSTS
AN ARM AND A LEG.
EVERYTHING!

36:58.694 --> 36:59.869
THERE'S INSURANCE...

37:00.000 --> 37:01.654
CITY FEES... STATE FEES...

37:01.784 --> 37:04.134
COUNTY FEES...
OH! AND THEN THERE'S LICENSES.

37:04.265 --> 37:06.702
AND PERMITS! I MEAN,
SO MANY PERMITS...

37:06.833 --> 37:08.748
AND SOME OF THESE
PERMITS... I MEAN,
YOU CAN'T EVEN GET 'EM...

37:08.878 --> 37:11.925
UNLESS YOU KNOW SOMEBODY
IN A HIGH PLACE. I MEAN,
SOMEONE LIKE GOD!

37:13.187 --> 37:15.798
GOLLY! AND BY THE TIME
I PAY FOR EVERYTHING...

37:15.929 --> 37:19.672
I'M NOT GONNA HAVE ANYTHING
LEFT TO FIX THIS PLACE UP
THE WAY I WANTED TO. OH!

37:19.802 --> 37:21.151
-OH, YES, YOU WILL.

37:21.282 --> 37:22.501
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN I WILL?

37:22.631 --> 37:24.372
-LIFE GUARDS TO THE RESCUE.

37:25.199 --> 37:26.809
-ALL: SURPRISE!

37:28.985 --> 37:30.248
-WHAT?

37:30.378 --> 37:32.293
YOU GUYS!
WHAT IS THIS?

37:33.555 --> 37:35.514
AH! THIS IS AMAZING.

37:35.644 --> 37:38.168
-THIS IS FOR YOU.
-WHAT COULD THIS BE?
I CAN'T--

37:38.299 --> 37:39.822
STEPHANIE...

37:40.780 --> 37:41.868
MY PERMITS!

37:42.477 --> 37:45.480
STEPHANIE GOT MY PERMITS!
HOW DID YOU-- HOW?

37:45.611 --> 37:48.135
-WELL, LET'S JUST SAY
WE KNOW SOMEBODY
THAT KNOWS GOD.

37:48.266 --> 37:50.355
-I DO HAVE FRIENDS
IN HIGH PLACES.

37:50.485 --> 37:52.182
-STEPHANIE, HOW CAN I THANK YOU?

37:52.313 --> 37:55.229
OH! HOW CAN I
THANK ALL OF YOU?

37:55.360 --> 37:56.839
-WELL, FREE FOOD'LL BE NICE.

37:56.970 --> 37:58.363
-OH, FREE FOOD?
LIKE, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA EAT?

37:58.493 --> 38:00.321
LETTUCE AND TOMATO...
THAT'S ABOUT IT!

38:32.266 --> 38:34.224
♪ WELL YOU PUT IN A HARD DAYS WORK

38:36.314 --> 38:38.054
♪ BUT YOUR BELLY AIN'T FULL

38:40.100 --> 38:41.884
♪ AND YOU NEED A FRIEND TO TALK TO

38:43.843 --> 38:45.627
♪ YOU NEED SOMEONE
TO CUT THROUGH THE BULL ♪

38:47.368 --> 38:50.197
♪ I SAID OH OH OH OH OH

38:51.764 --> 38:53.809
♪ OH OH OH OH OH

38:55.245 --> 38:57.509
♪ AND THE DOCTOR SAID YOU NEED IT

38:59.467 --> 39:01.556
♪ AND I THINK I NEED IT TOO

39:02.252 --> 39:05.168
♪ BABY I NEED YOU TO

39:05.299 --> 39:09.912
♪ FEED ME PLEASE
BELIEVE ME I NEED YOU ♪

39:10.043 --> 39:11.784
♪ OH YOU'RE SO GREAT

39:11.914 --> 39:16.832
♪ I JUST CAN'T WAIT
I NEED YOU ♪

39:33.501 --> 39:36.112
♪ BABY I NEED YOU TO

39:36.243 --> 39:40.769
♪ FEED ME PLEASE
BELIEVE ME I NEED YOU ♪

39:51.519 --> 39:53.260
-YOU THINK PEOPLE
HAVE A TRUE COLOR?

39:54.000 --> 39:55.436
-I DON'T KNOW, PAL.
I THINK THAT...

39:56.132 --> 39:59.353
COLORS KIND OF BLEND INTO
EACH OTHER DEPENDING ON
THE SITUATION.

40:00.398 --> 40:02.400
-RIGHT NOW I THINK
I'M PURPLE.

40:03.270 --> 40:04.402
-PURPLE? WHY PURPLE?

40:05.011 --> 40:07.100
-WELL, I FEEL A LITTLE SAD...

40:07.230 --> 40:09.189
AND THAT SHOULD BE BLUE.
-RIGHT.

40:09.319 --> 40:11.060
-AND I ALSO FEEL
A LITTLE HAPPY...

40:11.713 --> 40:13.976
AND I THINK THAT
SHOULD BE RED.
-RIGHT.

40:14.107 --> 40:15.717
-BLUE AND RED
MAKE PURPLE.

40:15.848 --> 40:17.153
-YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

40:17.719 --> 40:19.852
YOU KNOW, I KNOW A WAY
OF GETTING RID OF THAT BLUE.

40:20.418 --> 40:21.288
-HOW?

40:21.941 --> 40:23.377
-[LAUGHING]

40:31.167 --> 40:33.126
-HEY, OW! OW! OW!

40:35.389 --> 40:37.304
[END THEME PLAYS]
